    "original_title": "Brooklyn: Tillary St. - Jay St.",
    "text": "Tillary Street, west from Jay Street, showing more of the south side of the street. The 6-story white building is the Brooklyn Edison Company Building, at Pearl Street, and beyond that, across the \"El,\" is a corner of the United States Post Office. In the left background is the Montague-Court Building.\n\nView 1: June 2, 1931\nView 2: September 9, 1939\n\nView 1 shows the S.E. corner of Tillary and Jay Streets, Tillary being on the left, standing to Lawrence Street; Jay Street is on the right. The cleared area is the same as that seen on the right in view 1, where the building was razed.\n\nP. L. Sperr\n",
